[4] USA (Arizona): detention facility
Date: 27 Jun 2016
Source: ABC 15 [edited]
http://www.abc15.com/news/region-central-southern-az/other/arizona-health-officials-confirm-measles-case-at-eloy-detention-center-total-cases-at-20


The Arizona Department of Health Services confirmed another case of measles on Mon [27 Jun 2016] bringing the statewide total to 20. Officials said the most recent case was confirmed at a private detention facility in Eloy.

The potential exposure areas related to the newest case are in Mesa, Gilbert and Casa Grande. .... -[more]

According to the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention, symptoms usually appear between a week and 2 weeks after a person is infected. Signs include: high fever, cough, runny nose and watery eyes. Then white spots may appear in mouth and red spots appear on skin.

[Byline: Josh Frigerio]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The number of cases in this detention facility has been gradually increasing. It would be good for the facility to vaccinate individuals to prevent further spread of measles. - Mod.LK

[Complications from measles are more common among adults. Approximately 20 percent of those with measles experience one or more complications including diarrhea, ear infections, pneumonia, encephalitis, seizures, and death. Measles is extremely contagious; 90 percent of susceptible household contacts of a person with measles will become infected. Symptoms of measles include high fever, rash, runny nose, pink and watery eyes, coughing, diarrhea, and earache. The risk of death from measles is highest for adults and infants.

The US is experiencing a rise in measles cases related to unimmunized US travelers bringing the infection back from other countries - See more at: http://www.adultvaccination.org/vpd/measles#sthash.RgYiaE8e.dpuf

See map of USA (Arizona) at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=4317125,207 - Mod.LK]
